  "title": "Masseter",
  "body_html": "<b>Overview</b><br /><ul><li>Masseter is one of the muscles of mastication</li><li>One of the strongest and most superficial mastication muscles</li><li>It has two heads: superficial and deep. Both insert onto the ramus of mandible</li><li>Masseter is located in the parotid region</li><li>Note the parotid duct travels across its lateral surface</li></ul><br /><b>Origin and insertion</b>  <br /><ul><li>Origin: zygomatic arch</li><li>Inserts: ramus of the mandible</li></ul><br /><b>Innervation and action</b><br /><ul><li>Innervation: mandibular division (V3) of the trigeminal nerve (as are all the muscles of mastication)</li><li>Action: elevate mandible / close jaw</li></ul><br /><i>images showing anatomy of masseter and muscles of mastication</I><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti095b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti095.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></div><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti096b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti096.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></div><br /><i>images showing points of insertion of the muscles of mastication onto the mandible</I><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti098b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti098.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></div><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti097b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti097.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></div></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodymedia\"></div>\n\n\n<div id=\"categorynum\">1</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategorynum\">2</div>\n\n<div id=\"categoryname\">Anatomy</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategoryname\">Head & neck</div>\n<div id=\"mybody\">\n\n<div id=\"body_content\">\n<b>Overview</b><br /><ul><li>Masseter is one of the muscles of mastication</li><li>One of the strongest and most superficial mastication muscles</li><li>It has two heads: superficial and deep. Both insert onto the ramus of mandible</li><li>Masseter is located in the parotid region</li><li>Note the parotid duct travels across its lateral surface</li></ul><br /><b>Origin and insertion</b>  <br /><ul><li>Origin: zygomatic arch</li><li>Inserts: ramus of the mandible</li></ul><br /><b>Innervation and action</b><br /><ul><li>Innervation: mandibular division (V3) of the trigeminal nerve (as are all the muscles of mastication)</li><li>Action: elevate mandible / close jaw</li></ul><br /><i>images showing anatomy of masseter and muscles of mastication</I><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti095b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti095.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></div><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqm